            . I am son-in-law to Thomas Webster, a <rs id="t18270531-282-viclabel1519" type="occupation">gold-beater</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-282-victim1547 t18270531-282-viclabel1519"></join>, who lives in Porter-street, Newport-market. The prisoner was formerly in his employ. On the 18th of March I put 9s. 6d. into my desk, which I locked - it was Webster's money; I left the prisoner in the counting-house (he was not then in the employ) - next morning I found the desk wrenched open, and the money gone.</p>
